headline: Will D.R. Horton's (DHI) Increased Buybacks Signal Sustained Confidence or Mask Housing Market Risks?
summary: Earlier this year, D.R. Horton raised its fiscal 2025 share repurchase target to US$4.2–$4.4 billion and repurchased US$3.6 billion worth of shares to date, reflecting management’s confidence in the company’s future prospects. This expanded capital return program comes amid continued operational strength, but also highlights ongoing risks tied to rising costs and affordability challenges in the housing market. We'll take a closer look at how D.R. Horton's increased share repurchase plans...

headline: The Zacks Analyst Blog Highlights Toll Brothers, Lennar, NVR and D.R. Horton
summary: Toll Brothers has surged nearly 30% in three months, outperforming most peers - but with softer sales, incentive pressure, and sticky land costs, can the rally last?
